<subSubSection id="C3166561FFC3B569FF3985CEFCF850D5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336EAFFC3B569FF3985CEFEB45782" blockId="72.[189,334,909,935]" box="[189,334,909,935]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<heading id="D0FB8186FFC3B569FF3985CEFEB45782" bold="true" box="[189,334,909,935]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B978EAF8FFC3B569FF3985CEFEB45782" bold="true" box="[189,334,909,935]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336EAFFC3B569FF3985FFFCF850D5" blockId="72.[189,1399,956,1264]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Length of female 8.0 mm (male unknown). Dorsum pale yellow with reddish to ochraceous markings; pair of wide lateral reddish orange stripes extended from crown apex across pronotum, narrower median wedge-shaped stripe extended from crown apex to scutellum, pronotum with two pairs of indistinct longitudinal lateral brown stripes superimposed on red lateral stripes, forewing ochraceous, with costal margin in basal half yellow; venter uniformly pale yellow. Crown parabolically produced, slightly longer than pronotum. Forewing without supernumerary crossveins. Hind tibial rows PD, AD and AV with 23, 13, and 18 macrosetae, respectively. Female abdominal sternite VII with short acute projection posteromedially. Second valvulae slender, tapered through most of length, dorsal margin serrate distally, with teeth rounded and alternating between sides.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
